{"word":"αἰθαλόεις","slug":"αἰθαλόεις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>αἰθαλόεις</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:αἴθαλος'><el>αἴθαλος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>smoky, sooty</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b>; <el>κόνις αἰθ.</el> black ashes <i>that are burnt out</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>burning</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}